It
was
the
Children's
Hour

Washington
Square.

Sleepy,
lazy—yawning
in
the
afternoon

lay
the
houses

on
the
north

the
Square,

among

mountain.

some
strange
island

far
away,
only
dreamed-of
city
of
peace

Greenwich
Village
in
these
glorious
September
days
while

the
grass
is
still
green

the
leaves
of
the
trees
at

best.

few
social
